caption: I love their nachos and their burritos. Their passion sangria is tasty!

Its always a time factor for this location. I called in thinking that would help but i still ended up waiting and additional 15-20 minutes. As good as the food is- I would consider passing if they cant get their timing together.

Overpriced, horribly bland tacos. Had the chicken and pork tacos. Meat wasn’t seasoned and the rest of the taco tasted like nothing. Needed lime, cilantro, radish and some hot sauce like a real taco.  Empanadas were also terrible.  Try Los Tacos No. 1 for the real deal.
OMG the food is AMAZING 😋 this was our first time eating here and we ordered a little of everything and we don't regret it!! Worth every single penny!
Food was delicious huge portions and very well put together!! Didn’t take very long corn epanadas and steak quesadilla were awesome !!! The tacos and nachos we amazing !! Thanks guys great job !
Food was cold and the meat was clearly about to expire

Great food, great service, staff is friendly and welcoming. Something different in the neighborhood.  Glad that they have a meatless option.  I highly recommend this restaurant, but I wish they had dine in. They still gets an A+++ from me.

They gave me the wrong order. They said my name and the bag does not have a recipe where one can compare that you have the right order. I don't live close to the place so it was disappointing.  Regardless the food was tasteful. I will go again and highly recommend you check your order prior to leaving the place.
Good food

I’ve had these tacos 3 times and they are consistently great! I ordered the chicken quesadillas and it’s outstanding. Awesome work. It’s not easy to be in business and keep consistency. Giving credit were it due.

The quesadillas are huge and tasty. The empanadas were mostly pasty shredded meat with more potatoes than protein—not my preference. The tacos were a let down, pricey and only sold in 3s. The shell wasn’t soft enough to me and the meat was over cooked. The sauces are good though. I would come back for the quesadillas, not the tacos. Service is good. I wish they had margaritas. It’s an okay spot. It’s in the hood, but lures a lot of gentrifiers. I’ve had better and I’ve had worse. Seems like a hit or miss depending on when you go and what you order. I’d give them another chance.
It's all right but I like Taco Bell best
Tacos with tasting great presentation excellent service
Excellent food, efficient service.

Service was good and workers are enthusiastic. Ordered the steak quesadilla, chicken tacos and empanadas. Tacos were good empanadas good the quesadilla was some how cold which made it a bit too greasy for me but the taste was there. I will definitely give it a try one more time.

Best tacos I've had in awhile!! Food was fresh and so delicious. I appreciated the presentation of the food as well. Most taco places put your food in a aluminum foil or cheap plastic container and call it a day. The extra effort is the cherry on top. I also had the chips and salsa and churros. Yum yum yum! That was great as well!
Customer service A1. The food was good as well. I got there 10 minutes before closing time and it was still good. I forgot my mask at home and I was provided with one. I appreciated it alot.

This establishment is a big upgrade to the area which mostly has large corporate "fast food" choices in the area.  The type of food is of the quality (and price) that one would have to leave the neighborhood for.  One gets what they pay for.  My order which included steak tacos, empanadas and quesadilla were all much above average.  In my opinion the Quesadilla was the best item of the bunch.  In the age of pandemic where safety, speed and cleanliness are paramount--I appreciated being able to order online and have contactless/curbside pickup--about 40 minutes from order click to first bite (on busy Valentine's Day).  On Stanley Avenue, curbside could be a little tricky so make sure to time your pickup with care and caution!   As for the kind of food--this is a treat to me and my family so I wouldn't order this stuff just any old day but only for special occasions and I will definitely order from them again!
Quality food and excellent service. A great addition to the neighborhood. Good luck!
Great service even better food! Glad to see more great restaurants coming into the community.

I wrote this long review, & it got deleted somehow.  But let me just say, I spent $80 (plus a $3.00 tip), & I was  disappointed. The food was cold, & it wasn't that tastey. The Sangria was just okay. I was expecting so much more.I ordered quasidias, tacos, nachos & empanadas. My $83 could've been spent elsewhere. Honestly, I'm  a little upset, because I hate wasting money.
The food was great Loved it!!!
Definitely the best tacos I ever had. I ordered 3 fish tacos 2 chicken steak & shrimp
VERY friendly staff! Food is awesome! Will be visiting again to try different items from the menu!
The food is sooooo goooood! Best alternative to fast food, everything is fresh. My new go to.....

Happy I just discovered this place! Got a chicken burrito -- tasty and good size portion. Going to try everything on the menu -- burrito bowl, nachos, quesadillas,  tacos, empanadas -- yumm!! GREAT alternative to the fast food, Chinese food, etc in the area. Food tastes clean, fresh, and not greasy. I asked for no guac and they still included it, so that's why 4 stars not 5.
Great quality efficient service very friendly Food is bomb for reasonable prices

One day passing through Brooklyn with my boyfriend, we decided to stop here and get something to eat. We saw the menu and it looked so good we couldn’t wait to eat. It was about a 30 minute wait because they were making the food fresh. When we received the food and began to eat in the car, it was TERRIBLE! My boyfriend had chicken empanadas and they were sooo greasy and the texture was unlike any empanada I’ve ever seen or tasted. We also ordered loaded nachos to share which were COLD!! We ate the food as soon as it came out so we were confused to taste Lukewarm/ cold nachos with cheese and meat on it. Lastly, I ordered 3 tacos for $12 which was a great deal. I ordered shrimp , beef and a pork taco and was disappointed again:  the shrimp taco tasted like artificial shrimp and the beef was flavorless and greasy. The ONLY thing that was great to me was the pork taco: it was tasty and prepared well. This food didn’t taste that fresh at all for such a long wait to receive our “freshly” prepared food. I was highly upset and disappointed especially since this was my first meal of the day and I spent so much money in total for our food. I will never come back again. Sorry, but I do not recommend coming here to eat. I only got a picture of my tacos which is why there is only 1 picture.
Great service staff is friendly and the food was delicious
